The paper proposes a deep learning approach to video compression, which involves using variational autoencoders (VAEs) for sequential data and neural image compression. This suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of probabilistic models and entropy coding, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on deep learning and neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
